Shocking images show seals being shot and clubbed to death for their fur off the coast of Newfoundland . 
  Humane Society International says baby animals 'are dying a violent death for fur products nobody wants' This year's 'commercial hunt' is the world's largest annual marine mammal slaughter . 
  Newfoundland government has authorised killing of up to 468,000 seals for fur . 
  Sir Paul McCartney has called on Canada to stop the hunt . 
 